Mon Jun  8 12:55:54 UTC 2026 - malcolmlewis@opensuse.org

- Updated to version 0.9.0:
  + Notification system: optionally works as a notification daemon.
  + OSD system: optionally show OSD information through the new
    IPC system.
  + IPC over a Unix socket: a way to control ashell externally.
  + Internationalization: the foundation for localized formatting
    and translations.
  + Experimental animations: work-in-progress animation support.
  + Official iced: thanks to iced_layershell, we now use the
    official upstream iced instead of the custom pop-os fork.
  + Relicensed from MIT to GPL-3.0-or-later.
  + See CHANGELOG.md for more details.

